Sublocality: New York, Franklin Co., Paul Smiths
Locality: 5. Black Pond near Adirondack Park Visitor Interpretive Center - North 300 m from Black Pond.
Habitat: Mesic woodland, canopy gap from recent (5 years?) Tsuga blow down. Growing in 0.5 shade.
Description: These are 2 - 3 month old seedlings; Mature trees in area, huge (to 23.0 m) and with very shaggy bark. < 15.24 cm.
Collection Miscellaneous: Some Acer spicatum in area and some of these small seedlings may be that species. Collections made from ca. 20 plants.
Associated Taxa: Abies balsamea, Acer platanoides, Acer spicatum, Betula alleghaniensis, Cornus canadensis, Fagus grandifolia, Picea sp., Tsuga canadensis, Viburnum lantanoides
